 376, 382). 
G. ATTORNEY’S FEES AWARDS AND SANCTIONS 
1. General 
Attorney’s     fees     cannot     be     assessed     against     
governmental agencies in Family Law actions except 
when sanctions are appropriate pursuant to 
CCP § 
128.5 or FC §    271. (FC § 273 and FC § 3652). 
2. Bad  Faith  Actions May Result  in  Sanctions 
Individual attorneys can still be liable for fees under 
CCP   §   128.5   and CCP   §   128.7   for   improper   
behavior. Motions for sanctions must be heard by the 
IV-D    Commissioner    who    presided    over    the    
proceedings from which the sanctions motion arose. 
(Orange   County   DCSS   v.   Superior   Court   
(2005) 129 Cal.App.4th 798). 
