requires the custodial parent or   obligee to apply for 
derivative   benefits   after   notification   of   possible   
eligibility. 
i. Credit Against Support Obligation 
a) Any  derivative  benefits  received  by  the  
obligee   because   of   the   obligor’s   benefits   
must    be    credited    toward    the    support    
obligation.  (
FC  §  4504(b); IRMO  Hall  
and  Frencher (2016)  247  Cal.App.4
th
  23). 
