1. Orders  Nullified  During  Reconciliation 
A temporary support order is not enforceable during 
any period in which the parties have reconciled and 
are  living  together.  (
FC  §  3602).  For  permanent  
support orders, the obligor may seek equitable credit 
(under IRMO   Jackson) for   any   time   he   or   she   
reconciled  and  lived  with  the  other  parent  and  the  
