greater amount of money, the entire lien should be 
requested and paid. If the net settlement does not 
provide sufficient money to satisfy the LCSA lien, 
leaving the injured worker with a share less than half 
of  the  net  proceeds,  the  standard  approach  is  to  request  
the net  proceeds  be  split  50/50.  LCSAs  cannot  collect,  by  
way  of  a  LC  §  4903  lien,  from  a  settlement  if  the  only  
support  owed  consists  of  arrears  that  accrued  prior  to  the  
date of injury at settlement. 
 
