1.Ongoing  Support  Order  Continues
A  child  support  obligation  survives  the  death  of  a
custodial
    parent.    (IRMO    Gregory    (1991)    230
Cal.App.3d  112).  While  the  support  obligation  may
remain  legally  enforceable  after  the  death  of  the',
