Creditors 
The provisions of a confirmed Plan bind the Debtor 
and each Creditor, whether or not the claim of such 
Creditor is provided for by the Plan, and whether or 
not   such   Creditor   has   objected   to,   accepted,   or   
rejected the plan. (11 USC § 1327) 
