5. Required  Attachment  to  Orders 
FL-590A,  UIFSA  Child  Support  Order  Jurisdictional  
Attachment,  must  be  attached  to  court  orders  when  
the court must make a finding regarding CEJ. 
6. Loss of CEJ 
The state that issued the original child support order 
loses  its  CEJ  over  the  order  once  another  state  with  
FFCCSOA/UIFSA jurisdiction modifies the order. At 
that point, the modifying state becomes the state with 
CEJ.  (
