CA  court  must  schedule  the  matter  for  hearing  
and give notice to the parties of the date, time and 
place of the hearing. (
FC § 5700.606(c)). 
7. Defenses  to  Registration 
The  contesting  party  has  the  burden  of  proving  one  
of   the eight defenses to registration (FC §   5700.607(a); 
see  also  Willmer  v.  Willmer  (2006)  144 Cal.App.4
th
 
951  [trial  court  confirmed  registration  on  obligor’s  
motion to vacate registration citing, inter alia, lack of 
