order,  contending  that  pursuant  to  the  parties’  
marital settlement agreement, all matters affecting 
interpretation of that agreement shall be governed 
by   the   laws   of   Idaho.   The   Court   of   Appeal   
disagreed  holding  that  “parents  are  bound  by  
public  policy  extrinsic  to  their  own  agreements”  
and   because   application   of   Idaho   law   would   
“undermine   the   mandate   of   the   UIFSA,   it   is   
