4. Individual  Indian Monies  (IIM) 
Individual   Indian   Money   (IIM)   accounts   can   be   
encumbered with an order from a court of   competent 
jurisdiction.  (
25  CFR  §  115.601(b)(1)).   IIM   and   
“court  of  competent  jurisdiction”  are  defined  in  
25 
CFR § 115.002. 
5. Per Capita 
Some  tribal  ordinances  allow  enforcement  against  
per capita (individual distribution of tribal revenue) 
monies through the tribal court. 
G. HEALTH INSURANCE     
A child’s eligibility for Indian Health Service satisfies the 
requirement for health insurance, even when the child is 
receiving Medicaid. (OCSS Policy Interpretation 94-07). 
 PRACTICE POINT: Contact the tribe to determine 
whether it will honor an IWO against per capita monies.',
