Waiver 
A  request  for  a stay   does   not   constitute   an   
appearance   for   jurisdictional   purposes   or   a   
waiver of any substantive or   procedural defense. 
(
50 USC § 3932(c)). 
f. More      Additional      Discretionary      Stays      
Additional  stays  may  be  requested  in  the  same  
manner as above based on a   continuing “material 
effect”  of  the  servicemember’s  military  duty  on  
his or   her ability to appear in the action. (
