26 USC §   199A). The Qualified Business Income 
(QBI) deduction allows eligible taxpayers to deduct up 
to 20 percent of their QBI. In most cases, QBI is the net 
proceeds  from  the  operation  of  a  business  or  Schedule  
K-1  income  distributed  by  a  pass-through  entity.  QBI  
does not include income that is not directly connected to 
the  operation  of  the  business  (e.g.  investment  income  
such as capital gains or   losses or dividends, and interest 
income not properly allocable to a trade or   business) and 
W-2 income paid by the business. 
The   QBI   deduction   is   also   available   against   rental   
income if the rental activity is operated in the form of   a 
business  with  sufficient  regularity  and  investment  of  
time and effort. A safe harbor is available to individuals 
